  When Pinokio tried to run the very next command (uv pip install -e MagiAttention), it was looking for a MagiAttention folder inside app\MagiAttention, which doesn't exist. This caused uv pip install to throw an error and cleanly halt the rest of   
  the script.

  I have updated install.js to append && cd .. at the end of the Windows clone fix. Now, after the repository and submodules finish cloning, the shell will correctly step back out to the app directory so uv pip install -e MagiAttention successfully  
  targets the folder, and the script can seamlessly continue to torch.js.
